thread.title: Ko takes back No. 1 spot after nine-stroke win in Taiwan
thread.title_full: Ko takes back No. 1 spot after nine-stroke win in Taiwan | Reuters

author: Reuters
title: Ko takes back No. 1 spot after nine-stroke win in Taiwan
text:
Lydia Ko cantered to a nine-stroke victory at the LPGA Taiwan Championship on Sunday to take back the women's world number one spot from South Korean Park In-bee.
Ko started the final round with a four-stroke advantage and then carded a seven-under-par 65 for a total of 20-under, which also made the 18-year-old New Zealander the youngest player to earn 10 wins on the LPGA Tour.
(Reporting by Sudipto Ganguly in Mumbai; Editing by Peter Rutherford )
